    "narrative": "The heart of our lineup today revolves around the elite speed-matchup profile of **Corbin Carroll**, who leads the board with a massive 85.93 score against Burke. The intersection of a favorable right-handed matchup and the opponent's slow delivery makes **Corbin Carroll** an absolute lock for a multi-steal upside day. Similarly, **James Wood** (76.27) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.97) are must-starts against the weak arm of V\u00e1squez; both benefit from strong spot-in-the-order boosts and park factors that make them high-leverage plays. **Brice Turang** (74.50) and **Trevor Story** (74.11) also provide significant efficiency, with **Trevor Story** specifically seeing a massive 19-point bump from a soft matchup against the erratic Gil.\n\nDeciding between our bench depth was a challenge, specifically regarding **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, both of whom carry high ceilings but were pushed out due to the difficult matchup against the elite Early. **Giancarlo Stanton** (48.48) narrowly missed the cut; while his raw power is appealing, the 19-point penalty from the SP matchup made him a liability compared to the consistent efficiency provided by **Vinnie Pasquantino** (68.90), whose platoon advantage against Baz secured him the UTIL spot. We are also keeping a close eye on **Dalton Rushing** (56.38); while he remains in the lineup, a 42% rain risk creates a volatile floor, and he serves as our primary hedge if the weather forces a late-afternoon adjustment.\n\nLooking at the remainder of the field, **Kyle Karros** (60.78) successfully climbed into the lineup on the strength of a favorable park and SP matchup, successfully bumping **Max Muncy** (47.58) to the bench. While we are sacrificing some of the long-ball upside typically associated with our depth pieces like **Alex Freeland** and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, the optimizer favors the high-contact approach of **Jose Caballero** (54.16) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (57.35) for today\u2019s specific slate. We are avoiding any risks with the deeper bench, leaving **Austin Riley**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Luis Campusano**, and **Travis Bazzana** inactive as we look to preserve our precious game caps for higher-leverage matchups later in the week.",
